│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs inside SLP vectorizer while computing combined orders in     │
│ combineOrders(). The assertion is from BitVector::set(Idx) where Idx must be  │
│ within the bitvector size. Here, an out-of-bounds index (61) is being set on  │
│ a SmallBitVector of size 60, causing SIGABRT.                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The debug log shows the vectorizer building large bundles of xor/or           │
│ reductions, then entering reorderTopToBottom(), which aggregates reorder      │
│ preferences from various sources (gathers, alt shuffles, phis, external       │
│ users). During the selection of the most used order, it calls                 │
│ combineOrders(IdentityOrder, Pair.first) for identity and filled identity     │
│ orders. The stack trace pinpoints the failure in combineOrders() at setting   │
│ UsedIndices.set(Order[Idx]).                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ OrdersType can contain special values equal to the order size (Sz) to         │
│ represent masked/undef positions (as documented in fixupOrderingIndices).     │
│ Other parts of the code (e.g., when converting masks from stores) normalize   │
│ these by calling fixupOrderingIndices, ensuring indices are in-range.         │
│ However, combineOrders() currently assumes all Order and SecondaryOrder       │
│ entries are strictly less than Sz when not equal to Sz, and unconditionally   │
│ calls UsedIndices.set(Order[Idx]). In this reproducer, some Order elements    │
│ are greater than or equal to Sz (e.g., 61 when Sz=60), likely due to incoming │
│ reorder data not fully normalized, especially when aggregating identity-like  │
│ orders or external reorder data. As a result, combineOrders attempts to set a │
│ bit at an index beyond the bitvector bounds, triggering the assertion.        │
│                                                                               │
│ Given the semantics, combineOrders should be robust to out-of-range values    │
│ and simply ignore them (they correspond to masked positions). This mirrors    │
│ the handling in fixupOrderingIndices, which distinguishes valid indices (<Sz) │
│ from masked ones (>=Sz).                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit file llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines 5929-5943 in  │
│ combineOrders() to add bounds checks before accessing                         │
│ SmallBitVector::set/test with indices derived from Order/SecondaryOrder.      │
│ Specifically:                                                                 │
│ - In the first loop, only set UsedIndices for Order[Idx] values that are <    │
│ Sz.                                                                           │
│ - In the SecondaryOrder-empty branch, when filling Order[Idx] = Idx, leave    │
│ logic as is but rely on UsedIndices.test(Idx) which is in-range.              │
│ - In the SecondaryOrder-nonempty branch, ensure SecondaryOrder[Idx] < Sz      │
│ before testing UsedIndices and assigning Order[Idx] = SecondaryOrder[Idx].    │
│                                                                               │
│ Code adjustment suggestion:                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ static void combineOrders(MutableArrayRef<unsigned> Order,                    │
│                           ArrayRef<unsigned> SecondaryOrder) {                │
│   assert((SecondaryOrder.empty() || Order.size() == SecondaryOrder.size()) && │
│          "Expected same size of orders");                                     │
│   unsigned Sz = Order.size();                                                 │
│   SmallBitVector UsedIndices(Sz);                                             │
│   for (unsigned Idx : seq<unsigned>(0, Sz)) {                                 │
│     unsigned Val = Order[Idx];                                                │
│     if (Val < Sz)                                                             │
│       UsedIndices.set(Val);                                                   │
│   }                                                                           │
