│ The patch changes combineOrders to guard against out-of-range indices when    │
│ marking bits in UsedIndices, preventing the BitVector::set assertion by only  │
│ setting bits for values strictly less than the order size. It also adds a     │
│ similar bounds check for SecondaryOrder before testing/setting bits, ensuring │
│ robustness when masked/undef entries use the sentinel value (Sz).             │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch diff:                                                                   │
│ - In the loop marking UsedIndices, replace "if (Order[Idx] != Sz)" with "if   │
│ (Order[Idx] < Sz)".                                                           │
│ - In the SecondaryOrder handling, add "SecondaryOrder[Idx] < Sz" to the       │
│ condition before testing/setting bits.                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ This fix addresses the crash without altering assertions elsewhere.           │
│                                                                               │
│                                                                               │
